N:jeo
D:[jeo] Integrated AI orchestration. ralph+plannotator planning -> team/bmad execution -> agent-browser browser verification (agentui=agentation watch loop) -> automatic worktree cleanup. Supports all platforms: Claude/Codex/Gemini/OpenCode. Installation: omc omx ohmg bmad ralph plannotator agent-browser agentation.
G:jeo orchestration ralph plannotator agentation agentui team bmad omc omx ohmg agent-browser multi-agent workflow worktree cleanup browser-verification ui-feedback 오케스튤 계획 실행 검증 정리

U[5]:
  Automate the full flow for multi-agent tasks: plan -> execute -> browser verification -> UI feedback (agentui) -> cleanup
  Visually review and approve plans with ralph+plannotator before coding starts
  Execute agents in parallel via team (Claude) or bmad (fallback)
  Verify browser-based behavior with agent-browser (snapshot, screenshot, UI checks) - default behavior
  Run the same workflow plugin across Claude/Codex/Gemini/OpenCode

S[8]{n,action,details}:
  1,Install,bash scripts/install.sh --all (install all: ralph omc omx ohmg bmad plannotator agent-browser)
  2,Setup-Claude,bash scripts/setup-claude.sh (/plugin install oh-my-claudecode + plannotator hook setup)
  3,Setup-Codex,bash scripts/setup-codex.sh (~/.codex/config.toml developer_instructions + /prompts:jeo)
  4,Setup-Gemini,bash scripts/setup-gemini.sh (~/.gemini/settings.json hook + GEMINI.md instructions)
  5,Setup-OpenCode,bash scripts/setup-opencode.sh (opencode.json plugin registration + slash commands)
  6,Plan,ralph+plannotator planning: /ralph "jeo-plan: <task>" -> run plannotator in blocking mode (no `&`) -> Approve("approved":true) or Feedback -> replanning loop
  7,Execute,team first: /omc:team 3:executor "<task>" / if team unavailable: /workflow-init (BMAD)
  8,Verify-Cleanup,agent-browser snapshot <url> -> UI verification -> agentation watch loop on agentui (ack->fix->resolve) -> bash scripts/worktree-cleanup.sh

R[5]:
  Review plans first with ralph+plannotator - block wrong directions before coding starts
  Plannotator must run in blocking mode (no `&`) - enter EXECUTE only after "approved":true / if feedback arrives, replan
  agentui (agentation) behavior: blocking `agentation_watch_annotations` -> annotation ack->fix->resolve loop / HTTP fallback (Codex/Gemini/OpenCode)
  Claude+omc: team first / Codex·Gemini·OpenCode: use bmad fallback
  For browser-related work, verify UI behavior with `agent-browser snapshot` (default)
  Persist state across sessions in {worktree}/.omc/state/jeo-state.json

E[3]{desc,in,out}:
  "Full install","bash scripts/install.sh --all && bash scripts/check-status.sh","All components installed + all AI tool integrations verified"
  "Plan->Execute->Verify","jeo 'implement new feature' -> ralph plan -> Approve -> team execution -> agent-browser snapshot","Browser behavior verification complete and screenshot saved"
